    `safe_compensate/2` returned; these pairs are kept in **reverse call order**
    (i.e. the order in which compensations run, most-recent-completed first); and
  - prepend a `{:compensated, name, value}` event onto the reverse journal.

The function returns a `{compensation_results, jrev}` tuple, where
`compensation_results` is the keyword list of `{name, value}` pairs and `jrev`
is the updated reverse-order journal (still most-recent-event-first, to be
reversed by the caller). Note that `safe_compensate/2` already guarantees a
compensating function can never abort the chain, so `compensate_all/3` never
needs its own error handling.

